Hi. I have some nested if statements. VS gives me the option to automatically convert them to switch statements, but do so incorrectly for the innermost if.
I am using Visual Studio Community 2017, Version 15.9.22
and .NET Framework Version 4.8.03752

Here is the innermost if:

```
if (0 == w && 0 == x && 0 == y && 0 == z)
                        // Missing attitude
                        dtSeconds = 0;
                    else
                        QuaternionMath.Normalize(ref w, ref x, ref y, ref z);
```

Converted the innermost if to switch. Notice tha 0 == z was somehow ignored:

```
switch (w)
                    {
                        case 0 when 0 == x && 0 == y:
                            // Missing attitude
                            dtSeconds = 0;
                            break;
                        default:
                            QuaternionMath.Normalize(ref w, ref x, ref y, ref z);
                            break;
                    }
```

For context, here is my entire method:

```
